originalText.text: I had a wonderful experience getting my divorce here. I was guided each step of the way. Ken and staff make the process easy.

originalText.text: We The People is highly recommended for a variety of legal services including Will preparation. It is staffed by paralegals that know their business. My Will was created from a questionaire and after proofing it an appointment was set for the necessary signings. We The People provided witnesses and a notary to wrap things up nice and legal. The price was as advertised with no hidden charges. This paralegal enterprise is a gem for those of us with limited funds. I'm now at ease knowing my assets will go to the beneficiary of my choice. Thank you We The People.

originalText.text: I had been separated for about 12 years from my husband and each and every time I attempted to get a divorce it was always to much money and just difficult. I went to we the people on 14th Street met with Kevin and it was fast inexpensive experience. Highly recommend this company!

originalText.text:
I would advise against using WTP. Having an incredibly negative experience after interactions that were described as "not how they normally operate."

Throughout the process there was patience and cooperation on both sides allowing work through unusual circumstances.

However, as soon as they received their last payment things went awry. Asking ahead of time for whether my change of address would be an issue as to where my documents would be sent, they provided misinformation now resulting in what will be an error. However, they tell me it's not an issue because the documents aren't signed yet and I'm "getting ahead of myself."

Not only was I misinformed ahead of time, but then after addressing the concern, I had emails ignored for nearly a month, until finally calling and receiving rude and terrible customer service, denying emails and still no answer as to the misinformation and lack of resolution to an issue for paid services.

I cut my losses, called it a miscommunication and got off the phone as quickly as possible. I've worked in customer service for a long time and I'm an extremely patient person when it comes to customer service representatives, so I seldom write bad reviews. This could not be overlooked.

Stay away from this place and if you feel like you have no other choice, save all of your emails. Not like it will make much of a difference anyway.
